longBusinessSummary: KSK Energy Ventures Limited, a power project development company, develops, owns, operates, and maintains power generation projects in India. It operates in two segments, Project development and Power Generation. The company's operational power plants comprising KSK Mahanadi Power, a 3,600 megawatt (MW) coal based power plant in Chhattisgarh; Sai Wardha Power, a 540 MW coal based power project in Maharashtra; VS Lignite, a 135 MW lignite based power plant in Rajasthan; Sai Lilagar Power, a 86 MW coal based power plant in Chhattisgarh; Sai Regency, a 58 MW natural gas based power plant in Tamil Nadu; 43 MW Sitapuram Power, a coal based power plant; and Sai Maithili Power, a 10 MW solar power project in Rajasthan. KSK Energy Ventures Limited serves industrial consumers and utilities. The company also explores for natural/mineral resources; and engages in investment/financing activities. KSK Energy Ventures Limited was founded in 2001 and is based in Hyderabad, India.
